1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on proposing a secure and lightweight authentication protocol, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of the proposed protocol in a mobile network environment, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a key distribution protocol, which falls under the domain of distributed computing. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a protocol suite, which involves the design and implementation of software components, falling under the domain of software engineering. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the impact of the proposed protocol on the degree of service persistence, which falls under the domain of computers and society.
